title: Alphabet's Market Dominance and Raised Stock Target
text: Alphabet, the parent company of Google, has shown a strong market position with significant earnings growth and strategic investments in research and development. The company's stock performance is primarily driven by the dominance of Google Chrome, positioning Alphabet as a leader in the AI market. The projected revenue for Alphabet in 2024 is $340.61 billion. Alphabet's stock price target has been raised to $150.00 per share from $140.00 by JMP Securities, which also maintains Alphabet at Market Outperform. Furthermore, Alphabet has an average outperform rating with a price target range of $136 to $180, as per the data collected from Capital IQ. Traders and investors use our platform.
